rganisations increasingly fill gaps in support left by the state. Invaluable to those in policy and practice, the book recommends a combination of person-based and place-based approaches to tackle rural poverty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRural poorzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Rural.2bisacsh1 aChapman, Polly, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGlass, Jayne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNewby, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978144736712340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447367147?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447367147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447367147/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles